# Testing Rules

## Current Status
No test runner is configured yet. When testing is set up (planned: Vitest), follow the conventions below.

## What to Test
- Agent input/output contracts (Zod schemas) → always unit test
- Fact Sheet immutability guarantees → always unit test
- Name Registry validation logic → always unit test
- Pipeline orchestration (BullMQ job flow) → integration test
- API routes → integration test with mocked DB
- LLM agent calls → integration test with mocked Claude/OpenAI responses
- UI styling and layout → skip
- Static content → skip

## How to Write Tests
- One concept per test
- Structure: Arrange → Act → Assert
- Test descriptions: "should [behavior] when [condition]"
- Test behavior, not implementation — if internals change but behavior doesn't, tests should still pass
- Place test files next to the code they test: `foo.ts` → `foo.test.ts`

## Rules
- Mock at the boundary — external systems only (Claude API, OpenAI API, PostgreSQL, Redis, Clerk)
- Never mock the code you're testing
- A failing test must tell you exactly what broke and where

## Before Adding Tests
- Ask the user before installing a test runner
- Do not add test scripts or dependencies without explicit permission
